<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        TROUBLESHOOTING THE CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING THE CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM</title>
        <table id="hl1600608">
            <title>Troubleshooting the Cab Tilt Hydraulic System</title>
            <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.49in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.74in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="3" spanname="1to3"/>
                <thead valign="bottom">
                    <row>
                        <entry valign="bottom">
                            <para>Condition</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry valign="bottom">
                            <para>Possible Cause</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry valign="bottom">
                            <para>Remedy</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Lift cylinder will not retract or advance</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir low on oil.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fill reservoir - down position.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Crossed hydraulic hoses.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replumb and bleed system.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pressure build-up in both directions due to plugged orifice in pump. (Indicated by
                                high effort required on pump handle.)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect return line at pump (when the control lever is in "Raise" position, the
                                pull port is the return line. When the control lever is in the "Lower" position, the
                                push port is the return line) and catch the fluid in a container. If the cylinders then
                                move when pumping, the return orifice or screen in control lever cylinder is plugged.
                                Repair or replace pump.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged or broken line.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace hydraulic hose.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Worn or faulty seal in lift cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair or replace lift cylinder.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pump handle kicks up</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Outlet ball leaking.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair or replace pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pump functions only on last portion of stroke</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir low on oil.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fill reservoir - down position.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Dirt on inlet screen.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Clean screen and reservoir.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Inlet ball leaking.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair or replace pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab will not tilt</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab latch binding, fails to release.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Free up latch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir low on oil.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fill reservoir - down position.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pump does not build pressure:</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Operate system in both directions several times to dislodge dirt or foreign matter. If
                                this does not free system, either the pump or cylinders can be at fault. Repair or
                                replace.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Inlet ball leaking.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective O-ring on selector valve spool.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Relief valve improperly set or blocked open.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Small piston in cylinder ball check is by-passing fluid.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pump leaks between pump base and reservoir</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective O-ring on reservoir.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair or replace pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab latch does not release</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Loose or disconnected "Quick Connect" in fluid line and latch.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Tighten fitting.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Latch damaged.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair latch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pinched hydraulic line.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace hydraulic line.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Frame twisted due to uneven ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move vehicle to level ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab latch does not latch</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Release lever does not engage trigger.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Readjust trigger position.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check for frame side member twist due to uneven ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Move vehicle to level ground and recycle by raising cab a few inches and then
                                lowering.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab will not tilt to full tilt position</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir low on oil.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fill reservoir - down position.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir has a vacuum because of OVERFILLING.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove fill plug and with lever in LOWER position, loosen pull port hose at pump and
                                operate pump to remove excess fluid. (Fluid will flow from loosened connection.)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(If reservoir has been overfilled, the reservoir vent will relieve oil pressure but
                                will not allow air to return. If there is insufficient air above oil level, a vacuum is
                                formed and the pump will cavitate.)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab bounces or chatters during tilt operation</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab hinge pivot bolts loose.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Tighten pivot bolts 210 - 230 ft-lbs. (285 - 310 N&#8226;m) torque.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air in hydraulic system.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bleed system.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab bounces or chatters after going over center</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Cab hinge pivot bolts loose.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Tighten pivot bolts 210 - 230 ft-lbs. (285 - 310 N&#8226;m) torque.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air in hydraulic system. To check for excessive air proceed as follows:</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bleed system.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Operate control lever to both positions several times.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Count the number of manual strokes of pump handle with control lever in "Raise"
                                position until the latches open. An average system requires five complete strokes.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Hydraulic oil forced out of breather</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir overfilled.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Drain and refill to correct level - down position.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Oil leak at hand pump plunger</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged seal.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Repair or replace pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>One latch not secure</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Latch and pad out of adjustment</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Adjust latch and pads.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="1to3" align="center">
                            <para>In addition to the foregoing, the following items should be checked if the pump is the
                                air assist type:
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>No flow with air pump running</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reservoir low on oil.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Fill reservoir - down position.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Inlet ball leaking.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check ball and seat for chips. Clean and reseat ball to seat.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Relief valve improperly set or blocked open.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relief valve assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air pump will not pump</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air pump poppet stem stuck.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Free stuck stem so that it moves freely. Check stem seal.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective seal on large pump piston.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace seal.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Pushbutton ball will not unseat.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check ball movement and seat.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Low inlet air pressure.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Increase air supply.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air leak, air pump will not run</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective seal on poppet stem.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace air pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged O-ring on poppet stem.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace air pump.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged O-ring on air-inlet swivel.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace air inlet assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective seal on main air pump piston.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace seal.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Freeze-up in the air motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Operate air control button rapidly to dislodge frost or move vehicle to warmer area.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air pump will not stop running</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Defective seat in pushbutton.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace air pump button valve assembly.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Air leak at pushbutton</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged O-ring on pushbutton stem.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace O-ring.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Damaged O-ring on air valve body.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace O-ring.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
